6. I found your statement regarding &lsquo;murderers and rapists&rsquo; rather misleading as you portrayed Hong Kong as the hiding place for crime committers and there are a lot of them in the city, but failed to provide any evidence to support this statement. No statistic, no study from trusted authorities, nothing. Also, why would murderers and rapists hide in a place where the cost of living is so fucking high when there are other places with much lower cost of living and no extradition arrangement? Well, I can only say maybe common sense is not common.<br />
7. Murderers and rapists from foreign countries will not cease existence only because of the law is passed, and there is no proof that such a law would help eradicate them out of Hong Kong &ndash; active participation of other countries is much needed and there is no warranty of such actions. However, judging from how the Chinese government has been framing and jailing demo activists, as well as the poor human right conditions in China, the chance is high with the extradition law being manipulated and misused by the Communist Party as a way to crack down on those who speak against it.<br />
8. I don&rsquo;t speak perfect English but I guess English would be a language you preferred. Please accept my friend request and reply to me on your story. Let&rsquo;s debate!&rdquo;

